{
  "$schema": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/oasis-tcs/sarif-spec/main/sarif-2.1/schema/sarif-schema-2.1.0.json",
  "version": "2.1.0",
  "runs": [
    {
      "tool": {
        "driver": {
          "name": "parsentry",
          "version": "0.1.0",
          "rules": [
            {
              "id": "DOS-001",
              "name": "UnboundedFileUploadResourceExhaustion",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Audio file is fully read into memory before size check, enabling memory exhaustion"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/400.html",
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "CWE-400"]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "DOS-002",
              "name": "MissingRequestLevelFileSizeLimit",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "No Content-Length or streaming size check before reading file into memory"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/770.html",
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "CWE-770"]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "INPUT-001",
              "name": "MissingFileKeyValidation",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Accessing request.files['file'] without checking key existence causes unhandled 400 error"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/20.html",
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "CWE-20"]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "INPUT-002",
              "name": "FilenameNotSanitized",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Uploaded file buffer is hardcoded to 'temp.mp3' regardless of actual format, but original filename is not validated"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/20.html",
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "CWE-20"]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "MIME-001",
              "name": "MimeTypeBasedValidationBypass",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "File type validation relies solely on client-supplied MIME type, which can be spoofed"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/345.html",
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "CWE-345"]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "INFO-001",
              "name": "ExceptionDetailLeakage",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "ValueError exceptions are re-raised directly, potentially leaking internal details to API consumers"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/209.html",
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "CWE-209"]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "results": [
        {
          "ruleId": "DOS-001",
          "level": "warning",
          "message": {
            "text": "In AudioService.transcript_asr(), the entire uploaded file is read into memory via file.read() before the size check (len(file_content) > FILE_SIZE_LIMIT). An attacker can send a file much larger than the 30MB limit, causing the server to allocate that memory before rejecting it. This enables memory exhaustion denial-of-service attacks."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "api/services/audio_service.py"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 54,
                  "startColumn": 1
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "properties": {
            "confidence": 0.9
          }
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "DOS-002",
          "level": "warning",
          "message": {
            "text": "None of the three audio endpoint controllers (console, service_api, web) enforce a Content-Length check or use streaming size-limited reads before passing the file to AudioService. The Flask request.files object will buffer the entire upload. Without a WSGI-level or reverse proxy limit, this allows arbitrarily large payloads to consume server memory."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "api/controllers/console/app/audio.py"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 73,
                  "startColumn": 1
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "api/controllers/service_api/app/audio.py"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 57,
                  "startColumn": 1
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "api/controllers/web/audio.py"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 65,
                  "startColumn": 1
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "properties": {
            "confidence": 0.7
          }
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "INPUT-001",
          "level": "warning",
          "message": {
            "text": "All three audio controllers access request.files['file'] directly without first checking if the 'file' key exists. If no file is uploaded, this raises a KeyError (HTTP 400) with a raw traceback rather than the intended NoAudioUploadedError. The NoAudioUploadedServiceError check in AudioService only triggers if file is None, but a missing key raises before that."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "api/controllers/console/app/audio.py"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 73,
                  "startColumn": 1
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "api/controllers/service_api/app/audio.py"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 57,
                  "startColumn": 1
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "api/controllers/web/audio.py"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 65,
                  "startColumn": 1
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "properties": {
            "confidence": 0.85
          }
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "MIME-001",
          "level": "warning",
          "message": {
            "text": "File type validation in AudioService.transcript_asr() checks file.mimetype against an allowed list of audio MIME types. However, the MIME type is supplied by the client in the Content-Type header of the multipart upload and can be trivially spoofed. No magic-byte or file header validation is performed. An attacker could upload arbitrary content (e.g., a crafted binary) with a spoofed audio/mp3 MIME type, which would pass validation and be forwarded to the speech-to-text model provider."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "api/services/audio_service.py"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 49,
                  "startColumn": 1
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "properties": {
            "confidence": 0.85
          }
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "INPUT-002",
          "level": "note",
          "message": {
            "text": "In AudioService.transcript_asr(), the in-memory buffer is hardcoded with buffer.name = 'temp.mp3' regardless of the actual uploaded file extension or detected MIME type. While this prevents path traversal via filename, it also means that files validated as wav/m4a/amr/mpga are mislabeled as mp3 when passed to the transcription provider, which could cause unexpected behavior or processing errors."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "api/services/audio_service.py"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 62,
                  "startColumn": 1
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "properties": {
            "confidence": 0.7
          }
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "INFO-001",
          "level": "note",
          "message": {
            "text": "All three audio controllers catch ValueError and re-raise it directly ('raise e'). ValueError exceptions from deeper service layers may contain internal implementation details (e.g., model configuration, workflow state) that get exposed to API consumers in error responses."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
